place.name: STRADSETT
place.gazetteerText: STRADSETT, a parish in Downham district, Norfolk; 4½ miles ENE of Downham-Market r. station. Post town, Downham. Acres, 1,318. Real property, £2,130. Pop., 180. Houses, 34. The manor, with S. Hall, belongs to W. Bagge, Esq. The living is a vicarage in the diocese of Norwich. Value, £120.* Patron, W. Bagge, Esq. The church is good. Charities, £5. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
